=head1 DESCRIPTION

Details about the state of your ECR re-scan duration settings. The ECR
re-scan duration defines how long an ECR image will be actively scanned
by Amazon Inspector. When the number of days since an image was last
pushed exceeds the duration configured for image pull date, and the
duration configured for image pull date, the monitoring state of that
image becomes C<inactive> and all associated findings are scheduled for
closure.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 PullDateRescanDuration => Str

The rescan duration configured for image pull date.


=head2 RescanDuration => Str

The rescan duration configured for image push date.

 </p>


=head2 Status => Str

